00:29:50.940 --> 00:29:51.770
So Newton's Laws.

00:29:51.770 --> 00:29:54.270
He had three of them.

00:29:54.270 --> 00:29:56.900
And we're all pretty
familiar with the second.

00:29:56.900 --> 00:29:59.515
The first, though, is
called the law of inertia.

00:30:05.760 --> 00:30:07.780
And basically, the
first law says,

00:30:07.780 --> 00:30:11.360
if an object is motionless
in the absence of forces,

00:30:11.360 --> 00:30:12.030
what happens?

00:30:16.480 --> 00:30:17.410
Stays motionless.

00:30:17.410 --> 00:30:19.200
Or, if it's at some
constant velocity

00:30:19.200 --> 00:30:24.340
in the absence of forces it
stays at constant velocity,

00:30:24.340 --> 00:30:25.370
right?

00:30:25.370 --> 00:30:30.500
So these have been stated
many ways over the years.

00:30:30.500 --> 00:30:33.450
I'm just going to try to come up
with short ones for the board.

00:30:33.450 --> 00:31:05.000
So in the absence of
forces an object--

00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:07.580
a particle-- moves
with constant velocity.

00:31:07.580 --> 00:31:10.740
In fact, Newton only talked
about motions of particles,

00:31:10.740 --> 00:31:13.290
not as in little tiny things.

00:31:13.290 --> 00:31:17.160
Not about rigid bodies that
have finite dimensions.

00:31:17.160 --> 00:31:21.810
He thought of the planets,
appropriately, as particles.

00:31:21.810 --> 00:31:23.030
Second law.

00:31:23.030 --> 00:31:24.710
Second law, I won't
write it all out.

00:31:24.710 --> 00:31:26.890
But basically F equals ma.

00:31:26.890 --> 00:31:30.350
Their vectors equals
the time derivative

00:31:30.350 --> 00:31:31.547
of the linear momentum.

00:31:31.547 --> 00:31:33.130
That's what we know
as the second law.

00:31:33.130 --> 00:31:38.030
The sum of all the
external forces

00:31:38.030 --> 00:31:40.610
equals the mass times
the acceleration.

00:31:40.610 --> 00:31:43.460
Another statement
of the second law.

00:31:43.460 --> 00:31:44.646
OK?

00:31:44.646 --> 00:31:45.520
So you know that one.

00:31:45.520 --> 00:31:47.410
That's the one you're
most familiar with.

00:31:47.410 --> 00:31:48.200
Third one.

00:31:48.200 --> 00:31:50.006
What's the third one?

